summary:
An investment entity whose investment objectives are to: 
1. Achieve a consistent high real rate of return, comprising both income and capital growth, whilst operating within acceptable risk parameters set by the Board; 
2. Deliver a regular income stream for shareholders in the form of franked dividends; 
3. Preserve and protect the capital of the Company.

